children.subject:
120 is usually considered an easier upper div, idk enough about the others.

Based on your schedule I'm assuming you're gearing up for 189, in which case taking 127 some time soon would be useful.

<md>I would honestly recommend not taking 4 techs if you find your current schedule challenging in any way. IMO the 3 techs you're currently taking are light in comparison to what you plan on doing in the fall. If you're interested in ML then it's best to try and do your best in the 3 courses you already have planned</md>

history.content:
Right now I'm currently set on taking 170, 188, and 126 for fall. I either want to add on 161, 164, EECS 105, or 120. I know 4 techs are crazy, but I'm currently taking 61B, 70, 16B, MCB C61, Ugba 135, a decal, and a cybersecurity course, and still finding a lot of time to spare. I think I can handle the 4 techs, so my question is which of the 4: 161(Weaver), 164(Chasins), 105(Nguyen), or 120(Niknejad) have the lightest workload.

(P.S. interested in AI/Ml and robotics)
